name: TagTransparency

properties.name: OFF
properties.description: Turns off the on-screen display of transparency. Note: Does not turn off transparency when printing or exporting the file.

properties.name: LOW_QUALITY
properties.description: Displays basic transparency (opacity and blend modes) and shows transparency effects such as drop shadow and feathering in a low-resolution approximation. Note: Does not isolate page content from the background. Objects with blend modes other than Normal might appear different in other applications and output.

properties.name: MEDIUM_QUALITY
properties.description: Displays drop shadows and feathering in low resolution.

properties.name: HIGH_QUALITY
properties.description: Displays higher-resolution (144 dpi) drop shadows and feathers, CMYK mattes, and spread isolation.

properties.name: DEFAULT_VALUE
properties.description: Uses the default setting. For information, see display performance preferences.

description: Options for specifying how tranparencies are displayed.
